{
  "texts": [
    "The answer is \"yes\" for \"non-Bayesian\" PAC bounds (Bartlett and Mendelson, 2006), based on Rademacher complexity: there are empirical bounds on R(θERM)-R(θ *).",
    "In the PAC-Bayesian case, it is a little more complicated (unless one uses the bound to control the risk of a non-Bayesian estimator such as the ERM).",
    "This is discussed by Grünwald et al. (2021).",
    "We will now prove Theorem 4.3.",
    "The proof relies on Bernstein's inequality (Lemma 3.8)."
  ]
